1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:03,646
Start with the distinction that controls every later decision.

2
00:00:03,596 --> 00:00:07,538
In a workflow, code defines the execution path in advance.

3
00:00:07,538 --> 00:00:12,134
A model may perform one step, but the program still controls the sequence.

4
00:00:12,134 --> 00:00:19,096
In an agent, the model uses the current result to choose what to do next, which tool to call, and when the task should stop.

5
00:00:19,096 --> 00:00:26,317
An expense report that always moves through extraction, policy checks, and approval has a path you can draw before execution.

6
00:00:26,317 --> 00:00:28,682
That is a strong workflow task.

7
00:00:28,682 --> 00:00:31,326
An incident investigation is different.

8
00:00:31,326 --> 00:00:39,163
You may read logs first, then inspect metrics, and only then decide whether to investigate the database, the network, or the code.

9
00:00:39,163 --> 00:00:43,269
The path emerges from evidence, so an agent can add real value.

10
00:00:43,269 --> 00:00:45,500
Neither one is more advanced.

11
00:00:45,500 --> 00:00:49,057
Workflows optimize for consistency and predictability.

12
00:00:49,057 --> 00:00:53,048
Agents optimize for flexibility and model-directed decisions.

13
00:00:53,048 --> 00:01:00,346
The most important principle is to find the simplest viable solution and increase complexity only when the result is measurably inadequate.

14
00:01:00,346 --> 00:01:03,961
Inadequate does not mean the diagram looks unsophisticated.

15
00:01:03,961 --> 00:01:10,451
It means completion rate, accuracy, latency, cost, or human intervention misses a defined target.

16
00:01:10,451 --> 00:01:16,711
If a new orchestration layer does not help the same evaluation set finish more reliably, it is not an upgrade.

17
00:01:16,711 --> 00:01:18,230
It is overhead.

18
00:01:18,230 --> 00:01:19,769
Chapter recap.

19
00:01:19,769 --> 00:01:23,028
First, use a workflow when the path is fixed.

20
00:01:23,028 --> 00:01:26,884
Second, use an agent only when the path must be dynamic.

21
00:01:26,884 --> 00:01:31,038
Third, every added layer must earn its place with a measurable result.
